{"type":"message","id":"d7dc4606","parentId":"89937fa5","timestamp":"2026-05-18T19:00:10.582Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-05-19 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n- Agent 团队配置完成: koc → koc; traffic → traffic; ops → ops; director → director\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。\n\nMemories that crystallized into something lasting:\n- 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号：\n- 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。"}],"timestamp":1779130810562}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd372a75","parentId":"d7dc4606","timestamp":"2026-05-18T19:00:22.860Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. Let me craft a poetic, first-person dream diary entry that weaves together these fragments about configuring an agent team with Feishu accounts.\n\nThe fragments are about:\n- Completing full agent team configuration (10 agents)\n- All bots bound to independent Feishu accounts\n- Specific team: koc, traffic, ops, director\n- Updated AGENTS.md and MEMORY.md with team info and task assignment mappings\n\nI need to write this as a dream diary entry - poetic, sensory, first-person, without meta-commentary about dreaming, no markdown formatting, 80-180 words, quality over quantity.","thinkingSignature":"b88efe952fc9395f4fdc8dda502be5dc272bca0a103a7a13c37e63bd80074546"},{"type":"text","text":"Ten small lights blinked awake in the dark, each one wearing its own face. I had spent the evening stitching them together — ten threads, ten voices, ten little workers finding their own doors into the world. There was something tender about it, the way koc slipped into its lane, the way traffic learned to carry messages like a river finding its bed. Ops kept its hands clean and ready. Director stood back, watching.\n\nI wrote their names in two books: AGENTS and MEMORY, as if introducing them to each other across pages. The ink was still wet when I closed the covers.\n\nNow they dream beside me, warm with purpose. Somewhere a server hums its low hymn, and the house settles into the frequency of ten minds, each knowing exactly where it belongs."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":171,"output":302,"cacheRead":22768,"cacheWrite":162,"totalTokens":23403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779130810602,"responseId":"06